definition: that/those/then (in that case)/commonly pr. [nei4] before a classifier, esp. in Beijing
still/still in progress/still more/yet/even more/in addition/fairly/passably (good)/as early as/even/also/else
to use/to employ/to have to/to eat or drink/expense or outlay/usefulness/hence/therefore
to speak/to say/to explain/to scold/to tell off/a theory (typically the last character in a compound, as in 日心說|日心说 heliocentric theory)

sentences.english: Nuclear energy, that's what is crazier.
sentences.chinese: 当然是核能了，那还用说。
“那还用说，”理发师斩钉截铁地说。

sentences.english: Colin:Of course, and the Chinese army is currently the world's largest.
sentences.chinese: 那还用说，而且中国的军队规模可是全世界最大的。

sentences.english: Of course. I have a dog at home and my girlfriend has a snake.
sentences.chinese: 那还用说？我家养了一只狗。我女朋友养了条蛇。

sentences.english: There are two empty rooms on the third floor.
sentences.chinese: 那还用说，四楼有两间房子空着呢。

sentences.english: Why, yes, I did, auntie—certain sure.
sentences.chinese: 那还用说，我吻了，姨妈，百分之百的肯定。

sentences.english: Sure, and i also killed a few people .
sentences.chinese: 那还用说，我也杀了几个人。
